Forex Capital Markets Ordered to Pay $14.3 Million by Regulator

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-10-03T16:27:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/forex-capital-markets-ordered-to-pay-14-3-million-by-regulator.html
Forex Capital Markets LLC was ordered
to pay a $6 million penalty and restitution of about $8.3
million by the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission, over
claims the company failed to supervise diligently the handling
of more than 57,000 customer accounts.  The agency commented in an e-mailed statement.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  